Herve Tessler 

		
		EVP and President, International Operations, 

	
		 Xerox Corporation 	

 
Last Updated: 05/24/2017 



Executive Summary
Tessler is the Corporate Executive Vice President and President of International Operations of Xerox Corporation, since January 2017. In January 2017, Xerox completed the separation of Conduent Incorporated, creating two market-leading, publicly- traded companies. Most recently Tessler was Senior Vice President and President of Corpora 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Tessler in his twitter profile says, “Diversity, technology, innovation and leadership are my passion.”
He is the corporate executive champion for GALAXe Pride At Work, the LGBT Employee Caucus Group at Xerox.< 
Current Focus

Current role: In December 2016, Xerox promoted Herve Tessler to president of International Operations where he will shape the company's international operations strategy. The role will see Tessler steer the operatio 
Biographical Highlights

Tessler was born c.1964 in Paris, France.
He holds a Masters in law from Paris Assas University (1981-1985) 
Other Boards and Organizations

Member, Board of Directors member, A Better Chance (2015-Present)

 





